- [ ] **Step 3: Create `internal/apierror/apierror.go`**

```go
package apierror

import (
    "errors"
    "strings"

    "github.com/lib/pq"
)

// Sanitize returns a safe error string for 500 responses.
// lib/pq errors return pq.Error.Message — human-readable, never contains SQL text.
// All other errors are stripped at the first newline to remove stack traces.
func Sanitize(err error) string {
    var pqErr *pq.Error
    if errors.As(err, &pqErr) {
        return string(pqErr.Message)
    }
    msg := err.Error()
    if i := strings.Index(msg, "\n"); i >= 0 {
        msg = msg[:i]
    }
    return strings.TrimSpace(msg)
}
```

- [ ] **Step 4: Run tests to confirm they pass**

```bash
go test ./internal/apierror/...
```

Expected: PASS — all 3 tests pass.

