## Task 6: Auth HTTP Handlers

**Files:**
- Create: `internal/auth/handler.go`
- Create: `internal/auth/handler_test.go`

**Interfaces:**
- Consumes: `*gorm.DB`, `*email.Service`, `auth.*`, `apierror.Sanitize`, `middleware.UserFromCtx`, `models.*`
- Produces (all mounted under `/v1/auth/`):
  - `Register` — POST, 201, returns `{userId, email, name, token}`
  - `Login` — POST, 200 / 401 / 403, returns `{userId, email, name, emailVerified, token}`
  - `Me` — GET, 200 (requires auth)
  - `VerifyEmail` — GET, 200 JSON (not redirect — Server Action handles redirect)
  - `ResendVerification` — POST, 200 / 429 (requires auth)
  - `ForgotPassword` — POST, always 200
  - `ValidateResetToken` — GET, 200 / 400
  - `ResetPassword` — POST, 200 / 400

> No `Logout` handler — NextAuth manages session; no cookies to clear on the Go side.

