## Self-Review Checklist

- [x] Go 1.26 in `go.mod`
- [x] GORM v2 with pool: `SetMaxOpenConns(25)`, `SetMaxIdleConns(5)`, `SetConnMaxLifetime(5m)`
- [x] AutoMigrate on startup — no separate SQL migration files
- [x] Routes under `/v1/` — no `api` prefix anywhere
- [x] Plain JWT issued and validated — no `gf.` prefix
- [x] `token` returned in login and register JSON response — NextAuth stores it
- [x] No cookies set by Go service
- [x] `Authorization: Bearer` header read by middleware — no cookie auth
- [x] Plunk track events with event names from env vars — no inline HTML
- [x] `apierror.Sanitize` uses `lib/pq` error type — no SQL in 500 responses
- [x] `VerifyEmail` returns JSON `{verified:true}` — not a 302 redirect
- [x] CORS middleware via `github.com/rs/cors` — first middleware on chi router, origin from `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGIN` env var, `AllowCredentials: false`
- [x] `Subscription` model in `models.go` — `StripeCustomerID`, `StripeSubscriptionID`, `Status`, `CurrentPeriodEnd`; added to `AutoMigrate`
- [x] `internal/billing/handler.go` — `CreateCheckout`, `CreatePortal`, `GetStatus` all behind `RequireAuth`
- [x] `internal/billing/webhook.go` — `HandleWebhook` bypasses auth, uses `webhook.ConstructEvent` for Stripe-Signature verification
- [x] Billing routes wired in `main.go` — `/v1/billing/webhook` registered outside the auth group
- [x] `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`, `STRIPE_PRICE_ID` read from env — never hardcoded
- [x] Forgot-password always 200 — no user enumeration
- [x] Rate-limit check before resend-verification and forgot-password
